{"title":"2026 Bespoked UK Apocalypse Build-Off – John Watson","link":"https://theradavist.com/2026-bespoked-uk-apocalypse-build-off","date":1777356758000,"content":"<p><em>The <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/2025-bespoked-uk-apocalypse-build-off\" target=\"_blank\">Apocalypse Build-Off</a> returned to the 2026 Bespoked UK show this year. While there wasn’t as much carnage as the year prior, the event still brought out the playful creativity it’s known for…</em><span></span></p>\n<p><strong>The Radavist thanks <a href=\"https://www.brooksengland.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Brooks England</a> and <a href=\"https://www.schwalbe.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Schwalbe</a> for sponsoring our <a href=\"https://www.bespoked.cc/uk-2026\" target=\"_blank\">2026 Bespoked UK</a> coverage and our independent Reportage!</strong></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-73.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-73.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-73.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-73.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.bespoked.cc/visit#apocslypse-london\" target=\"_blank\">Bespoked</a>‘s Apocalypse Build-Off is thrown by <a href=\"https://www.brothercycles.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Brother Cycles</a> with help from the lads at <a href=\"https://sentient.works/\" target=\"_blank\">Sentient Works</a>. The contest is an invitation to play and to reconnect with a special kind of creativity that thrives within the confines of limitations. A space where, within those limitations, builders can be freaks and just have fun.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-74.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-74.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-74.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-74.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Open to individuals, builders, bike shops (or anyone who has a hankering to build a machine you can ride to hell and back), the Apocalypse Build-Off bicycles were showcased for Bespoked visitors in a dedicated section for the entirety of the show last weekend.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-76.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-76.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-76.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-76.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-79.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-79.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-79.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-79.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-77.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-77.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-77.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-77.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><em><a href=\"https://theradavist.com/sentient-works-project-xl-double-bacon-cheesebrother\" target=\"_blank\">Sentient’s XL Double Bacon Cheesburger</a> is the American SUV of the electric cargo bike world. </em></p>\n<p>Each bike addresses the criteria supplied by Brother Cycles in unique ways. For instance, these are the requirements:</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Apocalypse-Build-Off-Build-01.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Apocalypse-Build-Off-Build-01.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Apocalypse-Build-Off-Build-01.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Apocalypse-Build-Off-Build-01.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Apocalypse-Build-Off-Build-02.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Apocalypse-Build-Off-Build-02.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Apocalypse-Build-Off-Build-02.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Apocalypse-Build-Off-Build-02.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-51.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-51.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-51.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-51.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><em>Will from Brother Cycles waving the quarantine Jolly Roger flag… This zone is HOT for radioactivity!</em></p>\n<h3>The Apocalypse is Nigh</h3>\n<p>The year is 2028. What remains of the once-great city of London is now a wind-scoured wasteland of crumbling concrete, twisted steel, and radioactive dust. Acid rain falls without warning. Nature is not healing – it’s mutating.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-47.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-47.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-47.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-47.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-44.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-44.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-44.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-44.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Contestants have to collect buckets of radioactive waste from a park north of the Bespoked event and then deliver it to a disposal site. The bikes came crashing through a busy crowd that had gathered at neighboring bars to enjoy an afternoon, oblivious to the global threat to health and safety they were facing.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-14.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-14.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-14.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-14.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-10.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-10.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-10.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-10.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-11.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-11.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-11.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-11.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Against all odds, the good people at <a href=\"https://www.seabasscycles.co.uk/\" target=\"_blank\">Seabass Cycles</a> are in possession of the only known way of disposing of the radioactive waste slowly destroying our planet. The problem? It’s super unstable and must be brought to them delicately through the decaying remains of London by the only means of transport that’s still operable in the wasteland: the trusty bicycle.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-31.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-31.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-31.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-31.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-30.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-30.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-30.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-30.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-20.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-20.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-20.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-20.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Attendees from Bespoked, and honestly, random people off the street, joined in on the fun and cheered the builders on as they steered their Apocalypse-ready rides to glory and salvation. The route was self-guided and 5 km, through the busy Saturday morning streets of Peckham, to safely dispose of the radioactive waste slowly destroying our planet, earning points for challenges along the way as they deliver the deadly payload and save humanity.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-6.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-6.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-6.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-6.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-7.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-7.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-7.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-7.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-5.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-5.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-5.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Apocalypse-Build-Off-5.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>While the waste removal journey this round was a success, there is now a theory that a mutant alien is loose, taking the form of cuddly dogs. Of which there was an abundance at the Bespoked show…</p>\n<p>Until next year!</p>\n<p>When I asked Petor how he felt the Apocalypse went this year, he said: “… perhaps next year we make the event harder…”</p>\n<p><em>(Next year, I’ll muster the strength to shoot all the apocalypse bikes, too…)</em></p>\n<p><strong>We’ve got more on the way from the 2026 Bespoked UK in London!</strong></p>\n<p><strong>We’ve got a lot more on the way, so stay tuned…</strong></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/CoverageSponsoredby_Schwalbe_Brooks.png?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/CoverageSponsoredby_Schwalbe_Brooks.png?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/CoverageSponsoredby_Schwalbe_Brooks.png?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/CoverageSponsoredby_Schwalbe_Brooks.png?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><strong>The Radavist thanks <a href=\"https://www.brooksengland.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Brooks England</a> and <a href=\"https://www.schwalbe.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Schwalbe</a> for sponsoring our 2026 Bespoked UK coverage and our independent Reportage!</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h3>All of our 2026 Bespoked UK photos are in <a href=\"https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fo/ub22h6il3xptz4rylnp42/AEloQInROxd7SbFXSmyuPWw?rlkey=l5crjp8imc8scm6ufw7a478ug&amp;st=igwozq3p&amp;dl=0\" target=\"_blank\">The Radavist Dropbox</a> for builders to use.</h3>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/2026-bespoked-uk-apocalypse-build-off\">2026 Bespoked UK Apocalypse Build-Off</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://cms.theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"4bb843259684418cd095a6758f0513ade3f45342c17be66c618a1c9d3b5861a0","category":"Cycling"}